com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.component.web

Class WebCmsComponentsFormProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors.EntityViewProcessorAdapter
      • com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.component.web.WebCmsComponentsFormProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.EntityViewProcessor

    @Component
 @Exposed
 @Scope(value="prototype")
public class WebCmsComponentsFormProcessor
extends com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors.EntityViewProcessorAdapter
    Processor that renders a number of components as direct form controls. Useful if you want to create a single form that allows direct editing of a number of components, including optionally the members of a container (setRenderMembersIfContainer(boolean)).

    This processor is for example used to render the content components of a WebCmsArticle as if they are direct fields on the article entity.

    Should work with any entity that is a WebCmsObject, except possibly with other WebCmsComponents.

    Since:
    0.0.2
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
